==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Mediostapedial
<hw>Me`di*o*sta*pe"di*al</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>medius</ets> middle + E. <ets>stapedial</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>Pertaining to that part of the columella of the
ear which, in some animals, connects the stapes with the other parts of
the columella.</def> -- <def2><pos>n.</pos> <def>The mediostapedial part
of the columella.</def></def2>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Medioxumous</ent>⟦br⟧
